[SN]TITLE[SN]
Financial services firm IFDS creates 100 Stirling jobs

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
One hundred jobs will be created in Stirling following the expansion of a financial services company.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The announced by International Financial Data Services (IFDS) has been described as "fantastic news" by Stirling Council leader, Johanna Boyd.
The jobs will be in customer service, management and for technical specialists.
They will add to the workforce at the company's base in Craigforth.
Irene McGowan, director of operations platforms at IFDS, said: "With a healthy pipeline of new business across insurance, pensions, asset management and the broader financial services industries, IFDS is able to offer exciting career opportunities across a wide range of skill sets."
Scottish government business minister Fergus Ewing added: "Scotland's financial services sector is one of Scotland's key strengths and enjoys a great reputation thanks to the skills, experience and commitment of our workforce.
"I am delighted that IFDS recognises that."
